As an expert programmer specializing in Unity, I can provide you with the pseudocode to create a square object that connects two moving points, resizes, and rotates as necessary. This will be done using C# scripting in Unity.
```csharp
using UnityEngine;

public class MovingSquare : MonoBehaviour
{
    public Transform pointA;
    public Transform pointB;
    public Vector3 size;
    public Quaternion rotation;

    private Rigidbody rb;

    void Start()
    {
        rb = GetComponent<Rigidbody>();
    }

    void Update()
    {
        MoveSquare();
    }

    void MoveSquare()
    {
        Vector3 translation = pointA.position - pointB.position;
        rb.velocity = translation;

        // Resize the square
        Vector3 sizeDelta = pointB.transform.localScale - pointA.transform.localScale;
        rb.AddForce(sizeDelta * 100); // Adjust the force to your desired effect

        // Rotate the square
        Quaternion rotationDelta = pointB.rotation - pointA.rotation;
        rb.AddTorque(rotationDelta.eulerAngles * 100); // Adjust the torque to your desired effect
    }
}
```
This script will create a square object that connects two moving points, resizes, and rotates as necessary. The `pointA` and `pointB` variables are Transform references, and `size` and `rotation` are Vector3 and Quaternion variables, respectively, to define the size and rotation of the square. The `MoveSquare()` function is called in the Update() method and moves the square, resizes it, and rotates it based on the differences between the two moving points. Adjust the force and torque values in the `MoveSquare()` function to control the movement and rotation of the square.

